cause of bad loans made during president suhartos leadership and the country was seen as dangerous for foreign investment over the next four years farallon installed a new chairman and made necessary reforms after farallon sold its stake for a profit in  many other institutional investors began to look to indonesia for returns in the year before farallons investment in indonesia  million flowed into the country as foreign direct investment after farallon exited that number grew to  billion in  and  billion in  according to council on foreign relations economics fellow sebastian mallaby farallons investment was a blessing for indonesia according to institutional investors alpha steyer considers himself as a researchoriented fundamental investor not a trader in march  farallon announced plans to refocus its investing on risk arbitrage and credit wagers and lessen its equity exposure in addition the firm said it would disclose more information to clients to foster a more open culture at the hedge fund investment vehiclesedit farallon capital institutional partners  for farallons institutional investors to invest in investment historyedit in  farallon in partnership with simon property group and other hedge funds purchased mills corp a real estate investment trust companyedit in  it was reported that farallon capital was the largest hedge fund in the world in  steyer named the firm after the farallon islands off the coast of the san francisco bay area organizationedit tom steyer and andrew jm spokes act as the firms comanaging partners spokes was promoted to the position in  prior to his promotion spokes oversaw portfolio management and strategy for farallon exclusive subadviser noonday global management spokes opened farallons first international office in london in  farallon retains talent by giving enterprising professionals the opportunity to spin off and run new funds with farallon capital for example former farallon traders started noonday global management and chinarock capital using farallon money and back office support today farallon has  principals  managing directors and  investment professionals who oversee the firms daytoday operations and management officesedit farallon along with noonday global management operates offices in san francisco new york city tokyo singapore london hong kong see alsoedit hedge fund risk arbitrage tom steyer referencesedit  a b c d e f g adamson loch  february  steyer power institutional investor retrieved  august    adam zoia aaron finkel  january  getting a job in hedge funds an inside look at how funds hire john wiley and sons pp – isbn  retrieved  july    the  hedge fund  ranking institutional investor inc may     a b c d farallon website   a b c d e lashinsky adam  september  californias hedge fund king fortune archived from the original on  january  retrieved  july    a b c d mallaby sebastian  more money than god penguin press  accessdate requires url help  fabrikant geraldine  for yales money man a higher calling new york times retrieved    keoun bradley march   farallon discloses takeover talks with accredited bloomberg retrieved  july    sorkin andrew  farallon plans shakeup report says new york times retrieved    williamson christine december   farallon receives mixed messages pensions  investments retrieved  july    stephen todd walker  january  wave theory for alternative investments riding the wave with hedge funds commodities and venture capital mcgrawhill professional pp – isbn  retrieved  august    goldman sachs leads hedge fund management rankings pdf wall street letter  june  retrieved  august  permanent dead link  strasburg jenny farallon names spokes comanaging partner with steyer bloomberg retrieved   external linksedit farallon capital companies grouped at opencorporates v t e hedge funds investment strategy arbitrage  relative value capital structure arbitrage convertible arbitrage equity market neutral fixed income arbitrage  fixedincome relativevalue investing sta